[2[
Date: Wed 28 Sep 2022
Source: Valor [in Portuguese, machine trans., edited]
https://valor.globo.com/brasil/noticia/2022/09/27/sao-paulo-identifica-surto-de-meningite-vacinacao-e-recomendada-em-toda-a-cidade.ghtml


The city of São Paulo confirmed this Tuesday [27 Sep 2022] the death of a resident of the East Zone because of meningitis. The woman, who was 42 years old, lived in the Vila Formosa neighborhood, which, together with Aricanduva, in the same region, has already had 5 confirmed cases of meningococcal meningitis of the same type C in the last 2 months, which constitutes an outbreak situation, according to the classification of the Municipal Health Department. Due to the scenario, residents of Vila Formosa and Aricanduva are being summoned to go to health centers to be vaccinated against the disease.

Sought by Valor, the Municipal Health Department stated, via the press office, that it recommends vaccination for all residents of São Paulo at public payphones throughout the city. However, it informs that there is no reason for alarm and that vaccination is being recommended as a precaution.

According to data from DataSUS, from the Ministry of Health, vaccination coverage for meningococcal meningitis C is currently 42.5% in the capital of São Paulo and 52% throughout the national territory. In 2015, both were at 98%. "It should be clarified that throughout the city the number of cases has decreased this year compared to 2019, the year before the COVID-19 pandemic. From January until yesterday (26 Sep [2022]) 56 cases of meningococcal disease were reported throughout the capital. During the same period of 2019 (January to September) 158 cases of the disease were registered, that is, a reduction of 64.5% in the general scope."

According to the Municipal Health Department of São Paulo, the serogroup identified in the 5 victims is type C meningococcal meningitis.

As soon as the cases were identified, the Health Surveillance Coordination (Covisa) began to supply preventive medicines to people considered closest to the victims, such as relatives or inhabitants of the same house, in addition to the vaccination intensification in the region. According to the Secretariat, 7400 people in the region have already been vaccinated in the last 15 days.

The São Paulo Health Department clarifies that the vaccine is available in all Basic Health Units (UBSs) in the city and guides vaccination.

